title: 911 call audio for Feb. 18, 2023 shooting in Hacienda Heights

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: 911 call audio for Feb. 18, 2023 shooting in Hacienda Heights
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The 911 call audio for all calls regarding a shooting at 1500 block of Janlu Avenue in Hacienda Heights in the afternoon of Feb. 18, 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Welsh

title: 911 response "run sheet" for Feb. 18, 2023 shooting in Hacienda Heights

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: 911 response "run sheet" for Feb. 18, 2023 shooting in Hacienda Heights
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The database "run sheets" that report the dispatch, response and transport for a shooting at 1500 block of Janlu Avenue in Hacienda Heights in the afternoon of Feb. 18, 2023. I ask that the full runsheets, exported from the computer-assisted dispatch system, be released with all data fields included.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ben Welsh
